limerick_list.text:
Cuts of beef you'll find butchers prepare:
Rump and sirloin (delicious when rare);
Shin and brisket (they're cheap);
But (unlike pigs or sheep)
Cows don't merit a chop — that's not fair!

When old Noah stepped down off the ark;
When I stripped a birch, leaving it stark;
When I made my pooch mute
(I just muzzled the brute) —
Those were three different ways to debark.

Got the fantods—she's having a fit.
She looks fearsome, I'll have to admit.
From her eyes she hurls spears;
Sparks emerge from her ears;
From her loud-howling mouth dribbles spit.

As a sponge, Acanthella is tickly;
As a plant, it has seed-heads all prickly;
As a parasite's stage
Between egg and of age,
It might make your intestines feel sickly.

Bicoastal means east coast and west coast;
I can't say which one's the best-dressed coast.
They both have that thing
Known as funk, kitsch, or bling;
So wherever I am is the best coast.

On a fact-finding trip overseas
I established the facts, which are these:
It is cheap to buy drink;
The best gin there is pink;
And I'm roundly condemned, now, for sleaze.

I had foresight and backsight in line;
The cool hand on the trigger was mine.
It was more than a whim
To assassinate him;
So I pulled, and he's dead now, the swine.

Three estates of the realm we possess:
The Lords Spiritual, ready to bless;
Then Lords Temporal (peers);
Last, the Commons (loud jeers).
There's no fourth, though some joke it's the Press.

I really should call my masseuse;
I subjected my back to abuse.
Chopping wood's a mistake;
All my vertebrae ache,
But a backrub will get me all loose.

Some find formal dance parties great fun;
All these gala affairs, though, I shun.
My preferred type of sport
Is the everyday sort;
So let's ball, dear, but not go to one.

I see algae adapting with ease;
I see light in precambrian seas;
I see chlorophyll driving
The biosphere's thriving.
My mom sees the stains on my knees.
